               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-336-person1688">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BATES
               <interp inst="t18250915-336-person1688" type="surname" value="BATES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-336-person1688" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-336-person1688" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. William Richard Town, of <placeName id="t18250915-336-crimeloc1809">Bishopsgate without</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-336-crimeloc1809" type="placeName" value="Bishopsgate without"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-336-crimeloc1809" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-336-off1807 t18250915-336-crimeloc1809"></join>. Between eleven and twelve o'clock in the morning of the 6th of September, I was at the bottom of the shop, waiting on a customer; a woman came to the door and cried out -"Come forward, a woman has stolen a piece of cotton from the door." I ran forward, and saw the prisoner with this cotton under her arm, and part of it hanging down. I brought her back with it.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182509150125"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-336-person1689">
                  SARAH 
                  WALTON
               <interp inst="t18250915-336-person1689" type="surname" value="WALTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-336-person1689" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-336-person1689" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was going along Bishopsgate-street, and saw the prisoner take the cotton from the side of Mr. Town's door, and put it under her arm; a friend of mine, who was with me, went into the shop, and gave an alarm.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-336-person1690">
                  SAMUEL 
                  SHEPHERD
               <interp inst="t18250915-336-person1690" type="surname" value="SHEPHERD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-336-person1690" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-336-person1690" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer, and have had the custody of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Last Tuesday week I was passing down Bishopsgate-street, and saw this cotton laying under the confectioner's shop - I took it up, and this young woman said, "Let it alone;" I said I should not; it was as free for one as another - she then came out, and took it up - by the appearance that young woman is the person who took it.</p>
               <p>
